Here is the full **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit of `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs`.

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High     | 2           | 2              |
| Medium   | 2           | 2              |
| Low      | 0           | 0              |
| **Total**| **4**       | **4**          |

Framework: **MSTest 4.1.0** · Integration-test calibration: **applied** (`[TestCategory("Integration")]` detected)

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**Smell:** Conditional Test Logic (testsmells.org Smell #1)
**Test:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` — line 97
**Rationale:** `if`/`else` branching means only one path executes per run. If `loaded` is never a `PremiumUser`, the discount-rate assertion is dead code and provides false confidence. Not mitigated by integration-test calibration.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — one branch is invisible to test results
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Fix — split into two deterministic tests:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsCorrectName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("vip@example.com", "Vera", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = (PremiumUser)_repository.GetByEmail("vip@example.com")!;

    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** The `PremiumUser` branch may never run, giving the illusion of coverage without actually testing it.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Smell:** Unknown Test / Empty Test (testsmells.org Smell #4)
**Test:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` — line 113
**Rationale:** Executes 100 inserts but asserts nothing. MSTest reports this as "passed" even if every row is silently dropped. The name implies a DoesNotThrow intent, but that should be made explicit.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — "passing" means only "no exception thrown"
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
}
```

**Fix — assert the observable outcome:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    const int count = 100;
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(count, users.Count);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** A silent regression (e.g., INSERT becoming a no-op) will never be caught by this test.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Sleepy Test

**Smell:** Sleepy Test (testsmells.org Smell #3)
**Test:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` — line 87
**Rationale:** `Thread.Sleep(3000)` introduces a hard 3-second wait and non-deterministic timing. Academic severity is High, but **downgraded to Medium** per integration-test calibration — async coordination delays are more common in integration contexts. Still a smell because the 3 s wall-clock cost adds up and the delay may be too short (flaky) or too long (slow suite).

```csharp
// ❌ Current — blocks thread for 3 seconds
Thread.Sleep(3000);
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

**Fix — poll with timeout instead of sleeping:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay()
{
    var user = new User("dave@example.com", "Dave");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    // Poll up to 5 s, checking every 100 ms
    var timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5);
    var interval = TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100);
    var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
    while (sw.Elapsed < timeout)
    {
        if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
            break;
        await Task.Delay(interval);
    }

    Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
        "Notification was not sent within the expected timeout.");
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** 3 s × N runs = significant slowdown; if the notification takes 3.1 s the test becomes flaky.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**Smell:** Assertion Roulette (testsmells.org Extended Catalog)
**Test:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` — lines 35–38
**Rationale:** Four assertions with no descriptive message. When one fails, the MSTest output is `Assert.AreEqual failed. Expected:<Alice>. Actual:<null>.` — the developer must open the file and count lines to determine *which property* was wrong.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — four message-less assertions
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

**Fix — add assertion messages:**

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip correctly");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip correctly");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Database should assign a positive ID");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Slower triage — developers waste time identifying *which* property failed, especially in CI logs.

---

## Smells Scanned — No Findings

The remaining 15 smells from the catalog were checked and are **clean**:

| Smell | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean | In-memory SQLite — no external resource coupling |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean | No test exceeds 3 distinct production method calls |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean | `3` and `10` in count assertions are self-documenting (items just added) |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Clean | No `.ToString()` in assertions |
| Exception Handling | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in tests |
| General Fixture | ✅ Clean | `_connection` and `_repository` used by all 8 tests |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ Clean | No `[Ignore]` or skip attributes |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Clean | No duplicated assertion statements |
| Lazy Test | ✅ Clean | Shared `Insert` calls are setup, not the method under test |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Clean | Uses `[TestInitialize]` correctly |
| Default Test | ✅ Clean | Class is properly named |
| Redundant Print | ✅ Clean | No console output statements |
| Redundant Assertion | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| Resource Optimism | ✅ Clean | In-memory DB requires no external setup |
| Empty Test | ✅ Clean | All test methods contain executable code |

## Well-Written Tests Worth Highlighting

- **`DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`** — clean arrange-act-assert, single concern, clear null-check assertion.
- **`InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity`** — good concurrency test with proper `await` and a concrete count assertion.
- **`ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted`** — good use of `CollectionAssert.AllItemsAreNotNull`.

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|
| 1 | **Assertion-Free Test** — `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` | Add `Assert.AreEqual(count, users.Count)` | ~2 min |
| 2 | **Conditional Test Logic** — `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` | Split into two deterministic tests | ~10 min |
| 3 | **Sleepy Test** — `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with poll loop | ~10 min |
| 4 | **Assertion Roulette** — `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` | Add message strings to each `Assert` call | ~2 min |

Fix #1 first — an assertion-free test is actively masking potential regressions right now.
